<span class="line"><span style="--shiki-light:#0184BC;--shiki-dark:#56B6C2">print</span><span style="--shiki-light:#50A14F;--shiki-dark:#98C379"> "False"</span></span></code></pre>
<div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true" style="counter-reset:line-number 0"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><p>Thus, in Python all the continuous lines indented with same number of spaces would form a block. The following example has various statement blocks −</p>
